   Valable jusqu’au 25/10/2019Fondation Terre des Hommes
   Fondation Terre des Hommes

Base Administrator – Salah Al Din, Iraq

   Accueil » Offres d’emploi » Base Administrator – Salah Al Din, Iraq
   Description

   Position Start Date : 01.12.2019

   Duration : 6 months

   Location : 2 offices located in Tikrit and Shirqat – Salah Al Din
   Governorate – Iraq

   Terre des hommes does not set closing dates for this position;
   recruitment is on-going until the position is filled


   Tdh :

   Terre des hommes Foundation (Tdh) is the leading Swiss child relief
   organization, based in Lausanne (Switzerland). Every year our projects
   support more than 2 million children (3 million in 2016) and their
   families in over 35 countries. We are part of the Terre des hommes
   International Federation (TDHIF), with 9 other sister organizations in
   Switzerland, Europe and Canada.

   Tdh has been present in Iraq since 2014 with NFI distributions in Dohuk
   Governorate and in October 2015 launched unconditional cash assistance
   with the support of Swiss Solidarity. Since these first interventions,
   Tdh is now present in eleven districts (Anah, Al-Qa’im, Haditha, Tal
   Afar, West and East Shirqat, Tikrit, Baiji, Hawija, Kirkuk and Tooz)
   across four Governorates (Salah al-Din, Kirkuk, Nineveh and Al-Anbar)
   with operations in the two latter districts since 2017 as Tdh followed
   the frontlines to provide emergency assistance. Tdh was the first INGO
   to have field offices in Tikrit, Shirqat, Tal Afar and Anah.

   Tdh’s strategy consists on providing emergency assistance in
   hard-to-reach and newly accessible areas with an integrated emergency
   response to conflict affected people while building the capacity of its
   current response in areas where services are being re-established.

   Current donors: ECHO, OFDA, DRL, OCHA, UNICEF, MoFA of Switzerland,
   MoFA of the Netherlands, Swiss Solidarity.

   Operational field bases : Kirkuk, Tikrit, Shirqat, Tal Afar and Anah

   Coordination bases: Erbil and Baghdad


   Context :

   Under the supervision of the Field Coordinator, the Base Administrator
   carries out administrative, accounting and financial management of
   his/her base, in compliance with donor and Tdh procedures.

   He/she supervises accounting operations and cash management, and
   carries out budget follow up  in conjunction with the program managers.

   He/she is also one of those in charged with ensuring that Tdh’s Human
   Resources policy is properly implemented at the base. The Salah Al Din
   base is composed of 2 field offices located in Tikrit & Shirqat.


   Responsibilities :

   Administrative management of personnel:
     * Assists in welcoming and integrating new personnel, ensure they
       receive administrative briefing
     * Supervises the administrative management of personnel recruitment
       and hiring at his/her base
     * Supervises the archiving, handling and security of Tdh personnel
       files
     * Ensures that performance reviews are carried out according to
       defined procedure, and monitor the professional development of
       personnel
     * Applies the formalities related to sanctions / disciplinary
       measures and termination or breach of contract
     * Assists in defining and applying Tdh’s salary and social policies
     * Evaluates risks linked to changes in compensation and social
       policies
     * Conducts meetings and communication with personnel at base level
     * Tracks the cost of living
     * Updates the mission organization chart for the base

    Team management
     * Defines the needs of administrative personnel at his/her base, and
       recruits according to the allocated resources
     * Trains, supports and evaluates the administrative team at his/her
       assignment base
     * Plans and supervises the activities of the administrative team

   Cash-flow/bookkeeping:
     * Manages his/her base’s cash-flow and ensures that banks and cash
       boxes are well supplied
     * Manages transfers and monitors the security of funds
     * Formulates cash-flow forecasts with the Logistics Officer and the
       Program Managers
     * Validates all disbursements and commitments of expenditure, in
       compliance with Tdh procedures
     * Supervises account keeping at his/her base, and monitors cash
       balances
     * Monitors bank books for his/her base and supervises the safe and
       cash boxes
     * Prepares and supervises the monthly closing, review and integration
       of the accounting for his/her base
     * Verifies the accounting files before they are sent to coordination
       office.

   Budgetary / financial monitoring:
     * Updates allocation boards for his/her base
     * Updates and analyses budget follow up in conjunction with logistic
       and program teams
     * Makes connections between budgetary consumption and activity
       progress
     * Monitors functioning costs at his/her assignment base
     * Oversees adherence to donor administrative procedures
     * Support the Administrative Coordinator in formulating financial
       reports, budgets for new projects and carrying out audits

   Administrative management of the mission
     * Verifies and validates all contracts drafted at the base
     * Assists in selecting Tdh premises

   Reporting/communication:
     * Establishes and maintains relationships with local and regional
       administrative authorities, monitors regulations in force
     * Takes part in meetings relating to administrative aspects,
       represents Tdh on request and/or by order
     * Supervises the sending of administrative files to the Coordination
       Office
     * Ensures administrative and financial reports are sent to the
       Coordination Office according to Tdh administrative calendar

    Other
     * Agrees to comply with Tdh Code of Conduct and promotes Child
       Safeguarding policy
     * Reports serious cases of abuse on children that she/he would be
       aware of in Tdh’s intervention locations. Strict confidentiality
       must be respected
     * Adhere to and enforce current administrative regulations and
       procedures
     * Works in close collaboration with operational projects and
       departments


   Profile :
   Professional diploma or university degree in Accounting, Business
   Administration, Economics or Audit

   Preferably 2 years’ experience in a similar position

   Advance IT knowledge (hardware and software, Microsoft Office,
   Internet)

   Knowledge of SAGA and HOMERE softwares is appreciated

   Previous experience with an NGO is preferable

   Previous experience working in remote areas

   Required qualities: organized, sense of human relations, diplomacy,
   communication skills

   Desirable: proactive, autonomous, rigorous, analytical, willingness and
   motivation to work in an international and intercultural context

   Languages: Fluent in English (written and spoken), Knowledge of Arabic
   is an asset.

   Knowledge of Iraqi context would be a distinct advantage


   Salary :

   Expatriate contract under Swiss regulations 2’950 CHF (~2’550 €) < >
   4’300 CHF (~3’700 €) net /month according to experience x 13, Holidays:
   25 days per year. Local accommodation and transportation, Health
   insurance, accident and medical repatriation insurance, return flight.

   Duration 6 months, more if funding available.


   Tdh Global Code of Conduct and Risk Management Policies :
     * Fully complies with Tdh’s Global Code of Conduct and systematically
       reports any breach to the Code through the whistleblowing
       procedure: raises awareness within the Foundation on abuse and
       violence and the rights deriving therefrom, respecting the rights
       and dignity of children, members of the communities and our own
       Staff
     * Commits to respecting Risk Management Policies including:
       Safeguarding Policies (Child Safeguarding Policy, Policy on the
       Protection against Sexual Exploitation and the Directive on Staff
       Misconduct at the Workplace), Safety and Security Policy and
       Anti-Fraud/Corruption and Prevention of the Financing of Criminal
       Activities Policies
     * Commits to reducing the risk of abuse and harm by developing a
       culture of open and informed leadership within the organization and
       in our work with children and the communities in which we intervene
       in.


   We offer an exciting and varied work, useful and meaningful, in a team
   that wants to make a difference for vulnerable children.

   Are you interested? Do you want to face this challenge?


   Procedure :

   Please applying directly online:
   http://www.jobs.net/j/JoXCDpmc?idpartenaire=20002

   Application files sent through our official website will be processed
   only if complete (CV + cover letter). Additional documents (diplomas,
   work certificates, etc.) will be requested at a later stage.

   We will be in touch with the shortlisted candidates only in the
   selection process – with the large number of applications received, we
   unfortunately cannot provide personal follow-up to the larger candidate
   pool. Thanks for your understanding.

   For any questions you can consult the FAQ below the job advertisements.

   To know more about Terre des hommes: https://vimeo.com/253387418



   Ville Tal Afar
   Experience 0 à 3 ans
   Fonctions Autre
   Secteurs d’activité Autre
   Pays Moyen Orient, Irak
   Date de fin de validité 25/10/2019
   Retour à la liste des résultats

